name: WebGPU
description: An API for complex rendering and compute, using hardware acceleration. Use cases include demanding 3D games and acceleration of scientific calculations. Meant to supersede WebGL.

byNum.1: Can be enabled in Firefox with the `dom.webgpu.enabled` flag.
byNum.2: Can be enabled in Safari with the `WebGPU` feature flag.
byNum.3: Can be enabled in some Chromium browsers (on Windows, MacOS, Linux) with the `enable-unsafe-webgpu` flag.
byNum.5: Not enabled on Linux by default.
byNum.6: Only enabled by default on Windows.
byNum.7: Partial support refers to only being enabled by default on macOS 26 Tahoe or later.
byNum.8: Only enabled by default on Windows as well as macOS 26 Tahoe or later on Apple Silicon.
